Reasoning: The paper deals with generating structured reports from medical images, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach to learning visually-informative medical concepts, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as deep learning (DL) and probabilistic graphical models (PGMs), making cs.LG and cs.IR likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper uses the OpenI chest x-ray dataset, which is a multimedia (MM) dataset, making cs.MM a possible sub-category.
